Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the deployment and scheduling behavior for the IBM_kubernetes-storage system:

```plantuml
@startuml IBM_kubernetes-storage

actor User
participant "Kubernetes API Server" as API
participant "Scheduler" as Scheduler
participant "Kubelet" as Kubelet
participant "Container Runtime" as Runtime
participant "IBM Cloud Block Storage" as BlockStorage
participant "IBM Cloud Object Storage" as ObjectStorage

User -> API: Apply YAML manifest
API -> Scheduler: Schedule pod
Scheduler -> API: Assign node
API -> Kubelet: Create pod
Kubelet -> API: Request PV
API -> BlockStorage: Provision volume
BlockStorage --> API: Volume provisioned
API --> Kubelet: PV details
Kubelet -> Runtime: Create container
Runtime -> Kubelet: Container created
Kubelet -> Runtime: Mount storage
Runtime -> BlockStorage: Mount volume
BlockStorage --> Runtime: Volume mounted
Runtime --> Kubelet: Storage mounted
Kubelet --> API: Pod running

User -> API: Deploy app with S3FS
API -> Scheduler: Schedule pod with S3FS
Scheduler -> API: Assign node
API -> Kubelet: Create pod with S3FS
Kubelet -> Runtime: Create container with S3FS
Runtime -> Kubelet: Container created
Kubelet -> Runtime: Mount S3FS
Runtime -> ObjectStorage: Connect via S3FS
ObjectStorage --> Runtime: Connected
Runtime --> Kubelet: S3FS mounted
Kubelet --> API: Pod with S3FS running

@enduml
```